This returns a `tuple` of (`str`, `int`):

    def exampleFunc(variable):
        return &#39;Your Variable is&#39;, variable

It&#39;s **exactly** the same as:

    def exampleFunc(variable):
        return (&#39;Your Variable is&#39;, variable)

