This for the other hand concatenates the `variable` to a string, and returns that:

    def exampleFunc(variable):
        return &#39;Your Variable is &#39; + str(variable)

This is a correct way to do this, alternatively you could insert the `variable` into the string with [f-strings](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0498/) and return that: `return f&#39;Your Variable is {variable}&#39;`.

